<title>INDIA: India considering information technology pact.</title>
<headline>India considering information technology pact.</headline>
<dateline>CALCUTTA 1997-01-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>India said on Saturday that it was considering joining an agreement to eliminate all import tariffs on information technology goods by the year 2000, although it did not sign it last year.</p>
<p>India did not sign the agreement concluded during the World Trade Organisation's (WTO) ministerial meeting at Singapore, but can gain from it as its terms are not binding on all nations.</p>
<p>&quot;We are very keen on it. We do have an advantage in it,&quot; Commerce Minister B.B. Ramaiah told an international business conference in Calcutta.</p>
<p>&quot;But my electronics department said on some things they wanted more time (to reduce tariffs). We have not rejected (the pact). I have kept it on hold,&quot; Ramaiah said.</p>
</text>
